init_text:
Once upon a time there was an old mother pig who had one hundred little pigs and not enough food to feed them. So when they were old enough, she sent them out into the world to seek their fortunes. You know the story about the first three little pigs. This is a story about the 92nd little pig.

The 92nd little pig built a house out of depleted uranium. And the wolf was like, "dude."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I'll have to come up with another plan."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf thought, "I'll blow the house down with a nuclear bomb."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf found a bunch of dynamite and he brought it back to the house.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He lit the fuse and threw the dynamite at the house.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I don't know what you're trying to do, but you're not going to blow my house down.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You're not going to blow it down."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf was like, "oh, I see.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I'll wait until he falls asleep and then I'll sneak in and eat him."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf tried to sneak in quietly, but the 92nd little piggy heard the wolf and he woke up.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He said, "I've got you now, wolf.
